Pattern Matching for "instanceof" operator should be used instead of simple "instanceof" + cast
In Java 16, the feature "Pattern matching for instanceof" is finalized and canÂ be used in production. Previously developers needed to do 3 operations in order to do this: check the variable type, cast it and assign the casted value to the new variable. This approach is quite verbose and can be replaced with pattern matching for instanceof, doing these 3 actions (check, cast and assign) in one expression.